sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1519123
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: By inserting the DNA sequence of a desired protein in our part, you will be able to secret your protein, bind it to a Nickel column, and cleave off the desired protein from the tag in very few steps. The OsmY-tag will allow you to have your protein fold in the periplam and form disulfide bonds. Once folded OsmY also allows the portein to be secreted into the media, which contains significantly less portion of endesired protein. The media containing the construct can there be run through a nickel column for further purification. Once elluted from the column, one can add TEV-His protease to cleave the tag off the desired protein. By re-running the protein in a nickel column, the desired portein will elute directly, while the tag and the TEV-His will stay bound to the column.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Raoul Martin, Drew Dunham
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: OsmY comes from the MG1655 E.coli strain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: His
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: His-tag; fusion to proteins facilitates detection, purification, immobilization; NgoMIV / AgeI protein fusion part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kristian M??ller
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Gene synthesis by ATG:biosynthetics, optimized for expression in homo sapiens by iGEM-Team Freiburg 2008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Between BioBrick 1.0 sites this part is flanked 5' by NgoMI(=NgoMIV) and 3' AgeI(=PinAI) to facilitate in frame cloning for protein fusions.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ShortLinke
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This linker was used to connect two different parts. The sequence produced the aminoacids Gly-Gly-Ser-Gly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Freiburg Bioware09
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Oligos synthesized by sigma. Hybridized by PCR.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: osmY
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Osmotically induced protein Y shown to have exporting capabilities when fused to other proteins
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Zong, Felix Ekness

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712074
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 promoter (strong promoter from T7 bacteriophage)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: T7 promoter is very specific promoter which is transcribed only by specific T7 RNA polymerase. Usually this promoter is used in expression systems where T7 promoter is cotransfected with T7 RNA polymerase. That ensures strong transcription of desired genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Rok Gaber

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TEVsite
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
TEV cleaves the following AA sequence with high specificity:
* Glu-Asn-Leu-Tyr-Phe-Gln↓Gly
but:
* Glu-Asn-Leu-Tyr-Phe-Gln↓Ser
is also reported
Note, the part suggested by the Voigt lab, also contains 2 additional 1xGly flanks for increased accessibility.
See also:
* BBa_I712077 (TEV N-term)
* BBa_I712078 (TEV C-term)
* BBa_I712016 (myri+TEV site, Slovenia team igem2007)
* BBa_J64007 (Dan Widmaier, Voigt lab)

Dougherty et al. (1989): Molecular genetic analysis of a plant virus polyprotein cleavage site: a model. PMID: 2669323
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Raik Gruenberg
